1
00:01:29,420 --> 00:01:32,990
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:36,220
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:37,810
-Let's go!
-Dao.

4
00:01:37,830 --> 00:01:38,740
What are you trying to do?

5
00:01:38,740 --> 00:01:39,759
Taking you out of Lingya Tower

6
00:01:39,759 --> 00:01:41,640
to find an antidote for you outside.

7
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,039
Let's go!

8
00:01:42,039 --> 00:01:43,200
Dao, listen to me.

9
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:44,080
Listen to me.

10
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:44,770
Let's go.

11
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:46,420
If we fight our way out now,

12
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:47,530
before my snake venom is cured,

13
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:48,440
I'll be dead.

14
00:01:48,479 --> 00:01:49,740
Then what should we do?

15
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:51,979
Where can we get an antidote?

16
00:01:52,259 --> 00:01:53,300
Where is it?

17
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,430
But Yanzhi,

18
00:01:57,039 --> 00:01:58,640
if the snake venom
reaches your heart meridian,

19
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,759
it will be hard to remove it.

20
00:01:59,759 --> 00:02:01,290
If I were outside right now,

21
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:02,860
I would definitely have a way to cure you.

22
00:02:02,860 --> 00:02:04,790
But there's nothing here.

23
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:05,720
I...

24
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,570
Your snake venom...

25
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:16,600
What should I do?

26
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,520
Well,

27
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,320
it's fine.

28
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:19,920
Just let nature take its course.

29
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,300
Stop crying, both of you.

30
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,290
Let nature take its course?

31
00:02:22,290 --> 00:02:23,390
You are about to die!

32
00:02:23,390 --> 00:02:26,320
How can you tell me
to just let nature take its course?

33
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,040
Dao,

34
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,100
since I'm going to die anyway,

35
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,440
before I die,

36
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,480
can you grant me one wish?

37
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:36,480
What is your wish?

38
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,320
I will help you fulfill it,

39
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,650
no matter what it takes.

40
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:42,079
I've noticed you've always treasured
your tiger‑head hat.

41
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:43,480
I really want to know

42
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,360
why it is so important to you.

43
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,560
If you tell me,

44
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:49,590
I'll know what I'm dying for,

45
00:02:50,490 --> 00:02:51,960
and it will be worth it.

46
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,760
That's it?

47
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:55,920
Mm.

48
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,240
I'll tell you.

49
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,520
I sewed this hat

50
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,360
with my own hands...

51
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,720
for my child.

52
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:20,810
Her name is Doudou.

53
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,560
She is a girl.

54
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,480
She is very smart,

55
00:03:24,690 --> 00:03:25,860
very sensible,

56
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,180
and very cute.

57
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:29,900
In the past,

58
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:33,620
I was a washerwoman.

59
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,440
I made a living

60
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,090
by washing clothes for others.

61
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:45,550
Women like us who do manual labor

62
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,690
have always been looked down upon.

63
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
At that time,

64
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,220
the men who came to my shop

65
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,800
all treated me...

66
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:56,780
as a garment they could try on at will,

67
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,940
taking liberties with me as they pleased.

68
00:04:00,210 --> 00:04:01,330
Let go!

69
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,520
They teased and insulted me.

70
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:06,100
It was always like that,

71
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,230
and I got used to it.

72
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:09,260
You're back.

73
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:11,690
Later,

74
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,460
a constable in town

75
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,850
came to my home
with a few ingots of silver to propose.

76
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:21,010
My parents saw that he was generous

77
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,720
and agreed to the marriage.

78
00:04:25,690 --> 00:04:26,790
At first,

79
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:28,820
he treated me very well.

80
00:04:30,150 --> 00:04:31,770
I naively thought...

81
00:04:33,170 --> 00:04:34,630
I had found a good husband.

82
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,450
Who would have known

83
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:42,290
it was all bullshit?

84
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,300
When he saw I gave birth to a girl,

85
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:48,100
he was greatly disappointed.

86
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,159
He didn't even hold her once,

87
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,960
and he went out to seek pleasure.

88
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,640
That bastard

89
00:04:53,659 --> 00:04:55,870
beat and cursed me every day.

90
00:04:55,890 --> 00:04:57,280
He even developed a gambling addiction.

91
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,640
He sold every valuable thing in the house,

92
00:04:59,659 --> 00:05:02,790
completely ignoring
whether Doudou and I lived or died.

93
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:05,970
I could only wash clothes for others
during the day

94
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:07,570
and mend clothes at night.

95
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:11,210
After he took my hard‑earned money,

96
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,170
he even complained
the copper coins smelled of soap.

97
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,240
Later,

98
00:05:18,010 --> 00:05:20,010
his gambling addiction grew worse.

99
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:22,380
He even...

100
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:25,570
even sold Doudou for money.

101
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,330
Give me back my Doudou!

102
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:39,610
[Indenture]

103
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:10,980
So that's why you hate gambling so much.

104
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,080
So,

105
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,000
Dao, the reason
you want to get out so badly

106
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,560
is just to find Doudou.

107
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,480
Even if I spend my whole life

108
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,050
and risk my life,

109
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:22,540
I will go and find her.

110
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:25,140
Dao.

111
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,650
I believe

112
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:29,610
you will definitely find her.

113
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,440
Mm.

114
00:06:30,670 --> 00:06:32,080
Thank you, Nan Yanzhi.

115
00:06:37,090 --> 00:06:38,120
I'm sorry.

116
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:40,230
You did it all to help me,

117
00:06:40,590 --> 00:06:42,140
and you saved me so many times.

118
00:06:42,140 --> 00:06:43,600
You almost lost your life.

119
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,440
Actually, I'm already fine.

120
00:06:45,730 --> 00:06:47,400
That snake's venom can't kill me.

121
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,600
How is that possible?

122
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,440
What do you mean?

123
00:06:51,460 --> 00:06:52,980
I'm fine.

124
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,480
Look.

125
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,680
It's getting better.

126
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,460
Are you sure you're fine?

127
00:06:57,460 --> 00:06:58,920
Are you sure you won't die?

128
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,010
If you don't believe me, ask Man.

129
00:07:01,010 --> 00:07:01,860
It's true.

130
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:04,200
Yanzhi's wound is already healing.

131
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,840
She's out of danger now.

132
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,040
You lied to me!

133
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,960
You scared me to death!

134
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,040
Nan Yanzhi.

135
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:19,590
Thank you.

136
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:22,540
Alright.

137
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,130
Alright, alright.

138
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,620
Right now,
the most important thing for us is

139
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:30,620
to figure out a way
to survive tomorrow's death match.

140
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:32,100
Mm.

141
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:33,740
Yanzhi,

142
00:07:34,159 --> 00:07:35,760
have you thought of a new way?

143
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,159
Mm.

144
00:07:39,970 --> 00:07:41,490
But I still need you, Man.

145
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,200
Me?

146
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:55,659
We don't have much thatch left.

147
00:07:55,690 --> 00:07:57,570
I would like to get some from you.

148
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,400
Sure.

149
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,510
Thanks.

150
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:18,880
Ms. Kou. Let me help you.

151
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,480
No need.

152
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:21,580
It's okay.

153
00:08:21,610 --> 00:08:23,600
Let me help you. You get some rest.

154
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:26,690
Thank you so much,

155
00:08:26,690 --> 00:08:27,530
Miss Man.

156
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,360
It's nothing.

157
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:30,540
With my condition,

158
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:33,100
even washing clothes
is so difficult for me.

159
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,640
I feel really bad about it.

160
00:08:34,669 --> 00:08:36,360
There's nothing to feel bad about.

161
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:38,030
We are all in the death match together.

162
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,630
We're in the same boat.

163
00:08:39,909 --> 00:08:41,909
Of course we should help each other.

164
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:46,430
It's a pity that we're all going to die.

165
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,600
If everyone could think the way you do,

166
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,200
before we die,

167
00:08:51,580 --> 00:08:53,980
maybe we could
live a bit more comfortably.

168
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,370
You don't need to be so sad.

169
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,600
In addition to being sad,
what else can I do?

170
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,920
Once tomorrow arrives,

171
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,780
we'll have to accept our own fate.

172
00:09:06,690 --> 00:09:07,630
Ms. Kou.

173
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,600
To be honest,

174
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,900
there is a sure way
to win the death match.

175
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:14,420
Really?

176
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,580
Actually, it's like this.

177
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,840
Tu Ya.

178
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:24,860
Tell me how to win.

179
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,880
How would I know?

180
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:29,050
I just heard everything.

181
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:32,400
You told Jiang Man and the others
there is a sure way to win.

182
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,970
Then you should ask her.

183
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:35,560
Every time I killed someone,

184
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,620
they had a lot of complaints about me.

185
00:09:38,170 --> 00:09:40,720
Do you think they would tell me the truth?

186
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,080
I can tell you.

187
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,520
So...

188
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,160
can you remove the dagger first?

189
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,280
The token the mute servants hold

190
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,480
has two sides.

191
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,740
One side has engraved diamond patterns,

192
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:58,660
rough and uneven.

193
00:09:58,010 --> 00:10:00,750
[Token]

194
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,860
The other side is as smooth as a mirror.

195
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:03,590
If you look closely,
you can tell the difference.

196
00:10:04,130 --> 00:10:05,880
The smooth side means betting lower.

197
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:08,460
[Token]

198
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:09,600
The rough side means betting higher.

199
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:12,720
Is what you said...

200
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:15,080
true?

201
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,320
You don't believe me?

202
00:10:20,340 --> 00:10:22,380
Of course I believe you more.

203
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:23,370
Compared to you,

204
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:25,790
that person...

205
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:27,880
is more dangerous.

206
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:38,560
You mean... Jiang Man?

207
00:10:40,330 --> 00:10:42,480
You don't know her past.

208
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:44,260
But I

209
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,690
have seen her cruelty.

210
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,520
[Token]

211
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,520
Everyone, sorry to keep you waiting.

212
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:12,780
The final round of this death match

213
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:14,610
is about to begin.

214
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:15,350
Wait.

215
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,800
If we still split into pairs and compete
against each other in the third round,

216
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,300
it would be too boring.

217
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:20,130
Oh?

218
00:11:20,730 --> 00:11:22,130
Then what do you suggest?

219
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,320
How about...

220
00:11:24,610 --> 00:11:27,960
each of our two sides
sends one representative?

221
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,520
If we win,

222
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:32,760
all the female prisoners here
will go to the fourth level.

223
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:35,940
And if you lose?

224
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,440
If we lose,

225
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,200
naturally everyone else and I will stay,

226
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,360
at your disposal.

227
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,280
Mm.

228
00:11:42,930 --> 00:11:44,690
This bet is interesting.

229
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:45,670
But...

230
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:46,730
But what?

231
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:47,800
I wasn't asking you.

232
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,160
A matter of such importance

233
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,800
is not something you can decide.

234
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,840
Haha.

235
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,040
What a joke.

236
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,000
If I can't make the decision,

237
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:57,280
who else can?

238
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,060
Naturally...

239
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:02,130
Ms. Kou.

240
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:14,190
Me?

241
00:12:17,810 --> 00:12:19,920
I'm just a weak woman.

242
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:21,770
Without this crutch,

243
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,750
I'm afraid I wouldn't even make it

244
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,950
past the third level.

245
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:27,220
Why ask me?

246
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,720
You can't get out

247
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:31,450
because you simply don't need to.

248
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:32,820
Am I right,

249
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,790
Lord Voice-Keeper?

250
00:12:38,060 --> 00:12:39,140
Miss Nan,

251
00:12:39,170 --> 00:12:40,810
please don't make fun of me.

252
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:44,190
Ms. Kou, no need to be modest.

253
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:45,880
You're a voice-keeper,

254
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:48,040
yet you're willing to stay among us.

255
00:12:48,410 --> 00:12:50,460
You really have exceptional courage.

256
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:51,850
Miss Nan,

257
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:53,680
what do you mean?

258
00:12:56,370 --> 00:12:59,080
First, there are no calluses
where your hand holds the crutch.

259
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,770
That means your injury is not an old one.

260
00:13:00,770 --> 00:13:01,920
Having a crippled leg

261
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:02,840
and knowing no martial arts,

262
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:05,120
how did you manage
to survive the death match

263
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:08,050
from the bottom level
to the third level step by step?

264
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:15,480
They just took pity on me

265
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,680
because of my crippled leg.

266
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,280
Second,

267
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,320
he doesn't have

268
00:13:22,650 --> 00:13:24,440
a guiding ring on his finger.

269
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,640
Moreover,
Jiang Man went to your room last night

270
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:34,320
and deliberately told you
how to win the death match.

271
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:36,660
I said the token had engraved patterns,

272
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:39,040
but I didn't say
they were engraved diamond patterns.

273
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:42,090
Yet you mentioned it when you told Tu Ya.

274
00:13:45,980 --> 00:13:48,500
Did I say
they were engraved diamond patterns?

275
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:49,430
I'm afraid...

276
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:51,750
you misremembered it, Miss Tu Ya.

277
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:53,150
I didn't misremember it.

278
00:13:53,430 --> 00:13:55,960
And the answer you told me
was the exact opposite.

279
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:58,620
You never wanted me to leave here alive,
did you?

280
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,650
In our tribe,

281
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:02,080
those who don't keep their word

282
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,680
shall be publicly executed.

283
00:14:03,990 --> 00:14:05,920
You told her everything I told you?

284
00:14:09,450 --> 00:14:10,510
When did you two...

285
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,760
become so close?

286
00:14:15,530 --> 00:14:17,660
We haven't known each other for long,

287
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:18,950
